The Geiger counter has been a fundamental tool of science ever since, and thanks to the 1950 film "Bells of Coronado" (The Bells of Coronado) featuring strange cowboy scholars Roy Rogers and Dale Evans, it has become a part of pop culture:
Man: “What the hell is that?”
Rogers: “This is a Geiger counter that can be used to find radioactive minerals such as uranium.
