In the second quarter of 2018 alone, the number of reported cases increased by about 40,000.
The fact that the vast majority of newly infected people are sexually infected means a change compared to the past.
The disease has spread rapidly through transfusions of infected blood in parts of China.
However, health officials at a conference in Yunnan Province said that the number of such cases has since declined to nearly zero.
Despite this, the number of people living with HIV and AIDS in China has increased by 100,000 compared to the previous year.
Sexual transmission of HIV is a serious problem for the LGBT community in China.
Homosexuality has not been a crime in China since 1997, but discrimination against the community has been very strong ever since.
According to estimates in various studies, 70-90% of men who have sex with other men end up marrying a woman because of the country’s conservative values.
The disease spreads in these relationships in many cases due to inadequate sexual protection.
Since 2003, the Chinese government has provided universal access to anti-HIV drugs as part of a program to solve the problem.
